The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Healthy rise in L amp;T earnings
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                       Healthy rise in L amp;T earnings
          OUR CORRESPONDENT                              
	Mumbai, July 28: Engineering and construction major Larsen amp; Toubro (L amp;T) has reported a 33 per cent rise in net profit at Rs 502.44 crore for the quarter ended June 30, 2008, against Rs 376.85 crore in the corresponding quarter last year.        
	A healthy order book helped the company improve its gross sales by 53 per cent at Rs 6,993 crore.         
	Its order inflow rose 24 per cent during the quarter. The companys net profit for the quarter grew by a robust 70 per cent on a year-on-year basis.         
	According to a company statement, efficiency in project execution and effective cost management enabled it to report good growth in profitability.        
	The engineering and construction segment witnessed a 28 per cent increase in order inflows at Rs 10,516 crore during the quarter. The share of international orders was 13 per cent of the total inflow.        
	The electrical and electronics segment reported modest growth in its order book and sales despite a sluggish demand during the quarter. The segments sales revenue increased 7 per cent to Rs 578 crore for the quarter. Exports constituted 12 per cent of the segments revenue.         
	The machinery and industrial products segment achieved gross sales of Rs 634 crore, an increase of 50 per cent over the corresponding quarter of the previous year. The segment reported higher operating margins because of a good demand for valves, industrial machinery and welding systems.        
	With a robust order book, the company projected healthy sales growth over the next one to two years and is optimistic of maintaining a healthy order inflow in the near to medium term.        
	Hindalco profit        
	Aditya Birla flagship firm Hindalco Industries today announced a net profit of Rs 696.76 crore for the first quarter ended June 30, a 16 per cent growth rate over the corresponding period a year ago. The company had a net profit of Rs 598.62 crore in the first quarter of 2007-08.        
	Total income rose to Rs 4,862.19 crore in the June quarter from Rs 4,809.76 crore in the same period of the previous fiscal. A steep depreciation of the rupee against the dollar affected the copper business by about Rs 151.9 crore during the quarter, the company said in a statement.                                                                                                                                      
